					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-550755#post-1536164</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-550755/scp-1391#post-1536164</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 13 Aug 2012 19:11:37 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>wishun</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>1204404</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>&quot;&#8230;and will report any damage for immediate repair and further observation for subsequent attempted breaches.&quot;<br /> Is that damage to the perimeter or damage to the heads? My first impression was that something happens when a statue gets busted, but since there was no follow-up on that in the main body, I'm now thinking that it means the gaurds should watch out for fence-cutting. Since that is SOP for every security gaurd ever, I don't see why it needs to be mentioned here.</p> <p>I'd like to know why interior patrols aren't permitted. Maybe because all the interior gaurds are headstone candidates and it was bad for morale? That's the only possibility presenting itself at the moment, and it just doens't fit my vision of the Foundation for them to alter procedures because the gaurds find it &quot;spooky&quot;.</p> <p>Not perfect, but good enough for an up-vote.</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
